favorites.content: There is only one way to happiness and that is to cease worrying about things which are beyond the power of our will.
favorites.author: Epictetus

favorites.content: A wise man will make more opportunities than he finds.
favorites.author: Francis Bacon

history.content: To invent, you need a good imagination and a pile of junk.
history.author: Thomas Edison

history.content: But man is not made for defeat. A man can be destroyed but not defeated.
history.author: Ernest Hemingway

history.content: If one does not know to which port is sailing, no wind is favorable.
history.author: Seneca the Younger

history.content: Efficiency is doing things right; effectiveness is doing the right things.
history.author: Peter Drucker

history.content: Don't worry about people stealing your ideas. If your ideas are any good, you'll have to ram them down people's throats.
history.author: Howard H. Aiken

history.content: You need chaos in your soul to give birth to a dancing star.
history.author: Friedrich Nietzsche

history.content: The greatest danger for most of us is not that our aim is too high, and we miss it, but that it is too low, and we reach it.
history.author: Michelangelo

history.content: The only way to do great work is to love what you do.
history.author: Steve Jobs

history.content: You really can change the world if you care enough.
history.author: Marian Wright Edelman

history.content: The happiness that is genuinely satisfying is accompanied by the fullest exercise of our faculties and the fullest realization of the world in which we live.
history.author: Bertrand Russell

history.content: Only I can change my life. No one can do it for me.
history.author: Carol Burnett

history.content: A friend is what the heart needs all the time.
history.author: Henry van Dyke Jr.

history.content: Either you run the day or the day runs you.
history.author: Jim Rohn

history.content: Twenty years from now you will be more disappointed by the things that you didn't do than by the ones you did do.
history.author: Mark Twain

history.content: Love is the master key that opens the gates of happiness.
history.author: Oliver Wendell Holmes Jr.

history.content: The world is but a canvas to the imagination.
history.author: Henry David Thoreau

history.content: We are either progressing or retrograding all the while. There is no such thing as remaining stationary in this life.
history.author: James Freeman Clarke

history.content: You can only learn so much from books. You can only learn so much from education. Ultimately, it is the wisdom of God that will carry you through in the toughest situations of life.
history.author: Ravi Zacharias

history.content: Knowledge without justice ought to be called cunning rather than wisdom.
history.author: Plato

quotes.content: Stay positive and happy. Work hard and don't give up hope.
quotes.author: Anonymous

quotes.content: Every day may not be good, but there is something good in every day.
quotes.author: Unknown

quotes.content: The only way to do great work is to love what you do.
quotes.author: Steve Jobs
